Title : Beaver Cove (British Columbia)
Text : {{distinguish|Beaver Harbour (British Columbia)}}
'''Beaver Cove''' is a [[cove]] on Northern [[Vancouver Island]], immediately to the south of the junction of [[Johnstone Strait|Johnstone]] and [[Broughton Strait]]s.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/22713.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Beaver Cove (cove)"]</ref>  The [[Beaver Cove, British Columbia|community of the same name]] is located at the head of the cove, as was a now-former logging community, [[Englewood, British Columbia|Englewood]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/38117.html BC Names entry "Beaver Cove (community)"]</ref><ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/51438.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Englewood (community)"]</ref>  The mouth of the [[Kokish River]] is at the head of the cove, southeast of the site of Englewood.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25642.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kokish River"]</ref>  Also on the cove, on its southeast shore northeast of the community of Beaver Cove, is the community of [[Kokish]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25640.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kokish (community)"]</ref>

==Name origin==
Like [[Beaver Harbour (British Columbia)|Beaver Harbour]] near [[Port Hardy]], Beaver Cove was named for the [[Beaver (steamship)|''Beaver'']], a [[Hudson's Bay Company]] vessel that was the first steamship on the northwest coast of North America.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/22712.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Beaver Harbour (bay)"]</ref>

